peak my language?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">On average, an interpreter can be connected within seconds. However, occasionally all interpreters for a particular language may be busy. When this happens, please call back in a few minutes.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">4. How to use photo interpretation?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">You can send photos and had our interpreters translated for you. Tap on &quot;Camera icon&quot; during the call, you can choose photo(s) from your phone or tap on &quot;Take photo&quot; to capture a new photo. You may send more than one photo. Tap on &quot;OK&quot; in the top right-hand corner to finish.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">5. How to share a live video with interpreter?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">During the call with a live interpreter, tap on the &quot;Video icon&quot; to share a live video with the interpreter. You can tap the &quot;Switch&quot; button in the top right-hand corner to switch between the front and rear cameras.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">6. How do I change my YesPo ID?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">You can change your YesPo ID in your account. Open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, tap on your name or your profile photo, go to YesPo ID and change it. Attention: Your YesPo ID can only be changed once.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">7. How do I change the language of the app?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Open YesPo app, in the menu bar, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, go to Setting &gt; Language and pick your desired language.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">8. How can I check my YesPo account balance and transaction?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">You can view your YesPo account balance and transaction on YesPo app.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">View your account balance: open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, you can see your current balance at the &quot;Top Up&quot; section.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">View your transaction: open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, tap on Setting &gt; Transaction.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">9. Why I can&#39;t connect to YesPo?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">Usually, this is caused by a problem with your Internet connection or the settings on your mobile phone. You can try the following steps to fix your connection:</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">- Turn off Wi-Fi and back on.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">- Re-login to our app.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">- Connect to a different Wi-Fi hotspot.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">- If you are using Android Phone and Wi-Fi, check your Wi-Fi sleep policy in your phone.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">- Connect to your mobile provider and make sure your APN settings are configured correctly.</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\"><br/></p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">10. Is my personal information and the content of my interpretation kept confidential?</p><p style=\"text-align: left;\">All our interpreters have signed a confidentiality agreement with YesPo, which states that all information pertaining to YesPo&#39;s interpreting work remains strictly confidential. We regularly monitor the interpretation calls and sometimes record the calls for quality assurance purposes. However, we guarantee that the recordings and the contents of your conversations to any third party will not be disclosed without your authorization.</p>','1. What is YesPo?YesPo is a multilingual and cross-cultural communication app providing on-demand interpreting service. With YesPo, you can be instantly connected to a live interpreter whenever you need language assistance.&nbsp;2. Why do I need to verify my email?We want to make sure that we got your email address right. Meanwhile, verifying your email address with YesPo improves the security of your YesPo account.&nbsp;Verify your email address is simple: open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, tap on your name or your profile photo, go to Email, key in your email address, then tap on &quot;OK&quot; in the top right corner. We will send you a verification mail by your request. Please go to your mailbox to complete the verification process.&nbsp;3. How long does it take to reach an interpreter who can speak my language?On average, an interpreter can be connected within seconds. However, occasionally all interpreters for a particular language may be busy. When this happens, please call back in a few minutes.4. How to use photo interpretation?You can send photos and had our interpreters translated for you. Tap on &quot;Camera icon&quot; during the call, you can choose photo(s) from your phone or tap on &quot;Take photo&quot; to capture a new photo. You may send more than one photo. Tap on &quot;OK&quot; in the top right-hand corner to finish.5. How to share a live video with interpreter?During the call with a live interpreter, tap on the &quot;Video icon&quot; to share a live video with the interpreter. You can tap the &quot;Switch&quot; button in the top right-hand corner to switch between the front and rear cameras.6. How do I change my YesPo ID?You can change your YesPo ID in your account. Open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, tap on your name or your profile photo, go to YesPo ID and change it. Attention: Your YesPo ID can only be changed once.7. How do I change the language of the app?Open YesPo app, in the menu bar, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, go to Setting &gt; Language and pick your desired language.8. How can I check my YesPo account balance and transaction?You can view your YesPo account balance and transaction on YesPo app.&nbsp;View your account balance: open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, you can see your current balance at the &quot;Top Up&quot; section.&nbsp;View your transaction: open YesPo app, tap on the top left-hand corner in the menu bar, tap on Setting &gt; Transaction.9. Why I can&＃39;t connect to YesPo?Usually, this is caused by a problem with your Internet connection or the settings on your mobile phone. You can try the following steps to fix your connection:- Turn off Wi-Fi and back on.- Re-login to our app.- Connect to a different Wi-Fi hotspot.- If you are using Android Phone and Wi-Fi, check your Wi-Fi sleep policy in your phone.- Connect to your mobile provider and make sure your APN settings are configured correctly.10. Is my personal information and the content of my interpretation kept confidential?All our interpreters have signed a confidentiality agreement with YesPo, which states that all information pertaining to YesPo&＃39;s interpreting work remains strictly confidential. We regularly monitor the interpretation calls and sometimes record the calls for quality assurance purposes. However, we guarantee that the recordings and the contents of your conversations to any third party will not be disclosed without your authorization.','',1,'Colin Kuan (SF578)',1466128659,3),(1693,'70F41C7629A2D0AC868D5D45D4029009','http_about_0001','F914E4ABE447FDAC35FD649D10C1DAF1','web','en','About','About','',1,'Colin Kuan (SF578)',1466128659,3),(1694,'C3B2D8D43FFB1842F9F170CF1EF0BA2C','http_about_0002','FAC8342F0A1CA95C719F47FD3B2D2993','web','en','The World\'s Leading Human Translation Service','The World\'s Leading Human Translation Service','',1,'Colin Kuan (SF578)',1466128659,3),(1695,'CC47B9F40C9048463267B57828E540C7','http_about_0003','AE715FE2A68EC12B6061033E7600A4AA','web','en','<h3>YesPo<br><span>As your pocket translator, YesPo will always be there for you whenever you need.</span></h3><br>      <div class=\"feature_a\">        <h4>What?</h4>        <p>