software, forums, services through its website(collectively \"Services\"). In order to provide a full range of services, you need to download the YesPo mobile application and register for a YesPo account. In the course of these various offerings, we often seek to collect from you various forms of personal information. We may ask you to create a Personal Profile, which generally includes three sets of information:</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.1 Personal Data</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">This includes your personal data such as your gender, first, middle and last names, date of birth, country of domicile, native language(s), etc. This information may be accessed and viewed by others, as determined by your agreement on the specific privacy practices with respect to certain services.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.2 Contact Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">This consists of your email address and mobile phone number. Contact information will not be shown on your profile or other public places. If you permit the YesPo app to access the address book / contact list on your device through the permission system used by your mobile platform, we may access and store contact information retrieved from your address book.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.3 Transaction Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">We collect transaction details related to your use of our Services, including the type of services requested, the date and time of the services provided, amount charged and other related transaction details.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.4 Device Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">We may collect information about your mobile device, including, for example, the hardware model, operating system, preferred language, device identifier (IMEI), serial number and mobile network information.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.5 Additional Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">Interpreters are obliged to include their additional information, such as native/spoken language(s), education level, profession and related experience, a narrative description of themselves and a photograph. This information is stored on our systems, and may be displayed on their public profiles on YesPo.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.6 Recording and Use of Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">We may collect information from Users through the interpretation they perform using the Services. YesPo may listen-in or otherwise electronically record the interpretation sessions. By using the Services, you acknowledge and consent to the recording, retention, monitoring and your verbal communications with YesPo. The recording of any Services may be used by YesPo as stated in this Policy.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>1.7 Information You Provide about a Third Party</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">If you choose to use our referral service to tell a friend about YesPo, we may collect your friend’s name and contact information. We may also track the success of our referral program. Please be aware that when you refer a friend, your name and phone number may be included in the message sent to your friend.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			\r\n			<li>\r\n				<h3>How We Collect and Use Your Information</h3>\r\n				<p>i）In order to provide, maintain and improve our services, including, for example, interpretation services, payment, sending invoices, providing products and services (and sending related news), developing new functions, providing customer support, developing security functions, verifying the identity of users, sending product update news and management messages;</p>\r\n				<p>ii）To perform internal operations, including, for example, preventing fraud and abuse of services; troubleshooting software errors and operational problems; performing data analysis, testing and research; monitoring and analyzing usage and activity trends;</p>\r\n				<p>iii)Where possible and in compliance with the local laws and regulations, send information which we believe may be of interest to users, including information related to the products, services and activities of YesPo, and discounts.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>2.1 Mobile Data</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">When you use certain features of the Platform, in particular our mobile applications, we may receive, store and process different types of information about your location, including general information (e.g. IP address, ZIP/post code, country code) and more specific information.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>2.2 Log Data</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">We may also receive, store and process Log Data, which is information automatically recorded by our servers whenever you access or use the Platform, regardless of whether you are registered with YesPo or logged into your YesPo account, such as your IP Address, the date and time you access or use the Platform, the hardware and software you are using, referring and exit pages and URLs, the number of clicks, pages viewed and the order of those pages, and the amount of time spent on particular pages.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>2.3 Cookies and Historical Information</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">Each time you access the Services, various information is gathered automatically, such as the domain, computer platform, browser type, IP address and place of origin. We gather this information in order to administer and optimize the Services for you and to diagnose problems with our Services and enhance your user experience.</p>\r\n				\r\n				<h5>2.4 Your Card Details</h5>\r\n				<p class=\"pcent\">Your card information is processed through secure server(s), and transferred internally with the protection of strong encryption tools available. Your personal details will not be sold or made available to anyone else and your card details are only known by our order processors.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			\r\n			<li>\r\n				<h3>Sharing and Protection of Information</h3>\r\n				<p>We will not disclose your personal information to any third party, except under the following circumstances:</p>\r\n				<p>\r\n					(a) You authorize us to do so;<br>\r\n					(b) To comply with law enforcement officials, government authorities or other third parties;<br>\r\n					(c) When required in order to complete mergence, acquisition, selling, restructuring or financing of the company in whole or in part, or during consultation of these matters;<br>\r\n					(d) It is required to fulfill your requests for our products or services, and perform related services, including but not limited to billing and receipt of payment;<br>\r\n					(e) It is required to provide information, special promotions, or promotional activities to which you agreed;<br>\r\n					(f) If we believe your behavior is not consistent with our terms or policies;<br>\r\n					(g) In order to protect the rights, property or safety of YesPo or other parties.\r\n				</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			\r\n			<li>\r\n				<h3>Updating Your Information</h3>\r\n				<p>If you want to update or correct inaccuracies in your information, you can log into your account and modify them any time on your own initiative. In the unlikely event of certain information items you cannot update through our system, please contact our Customer Support Team for assistance.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			\r\n			<li>\r\n				<h3>International Data Transfer</h3>\r\n				<p>We may transfer personal information that we collect about you to affiliated entities or to other third parties across borders and from your country or jurisdiction to other countries or jurisdictions around the world for the purposes of processing or storage. Some of these countries may not have the same level of data protection as afforded by the laws in your home country. However, when we transfer your personal information, we will take steps to ensure it is treated in accordance with our Privacy Policy.</p>\r\n			</li>\r\n			\r\n			<li>\r\n				<h3>Technical and/or Operational Security</h3>\r\n				<p>We respect and recognize that personal data are vulnerable to security breaches which, if taken place, may caus